{"key":"processedPost-11865931","value":{"id":11865931,"first":11865179,"last":13457824,"when":1264020069,"utime":"01/20/10 10:41 PM","cleanedPost":"You'll want to use about 550 to 600 ml for those 20 dishes. 3 1/2 tablespoons of FP pre-mix is correct for that amount of water.&nbsp; I'd suggest a 750ml whiskey bottle for the agar.&nbsp; The long neck makes it a lot easier to pour, and the smaller diameter opening makes it less likely that contaminants will enter as your pour.&nbsp; Drill a hole in the lid, and then place a piece of tyvek over the bottle before screwing the lid on.&nbsp; Cover with foil and sterilize 45 minutes at 15 psi.<br />RR"}}